User Stories
US-01: Student Registration and Profile Creation
Actor
Student
User Story
As a student, I want to register and create my profile so that I can participate in placement activities.
Preconditions
•	Student must have a valid institutional email ID.
•	The platform must be accessible.
Main Flow
1.	Student opens the registration page.
2.	Student enters personal and academic details.
3.	Student uploads required documents.
4.	System validates the information.
5.	System creates the student profile.
Postconditions
•	Student account is successfully created.
•	Profile information is stored in the system.
Acceptance Criteria
•	Student can log in after registration.
•	All mandatory fields must be completed.

US-02: Resume Upload
Actor
Student
User Story
As a student, I want to upload my resume so that recruiters can review my qualifications.
Preconditions
•	Student must be logged in.
•	Student profile must exist.
Main Flow
1.	Student navigates to the Resume section.
2.	Student selects a resume file.
3.	Student uploads the file.
4.	System validates the file format.
5.	Resume is stored successfully.
Postconditions
•	Resume becomes available to recruiters.
Acceptance Criteria
•	PDF and DOCX formats are supported.
•	Upload confirmation is displayed.

US-03: AI-Based Job Recommendation
Actor
Student
User Story
As a student, I want AI-based job recommendations so that I can find jobs matching my skills and interests.
Preconditions
•	Student profile is completed.
•	Skills and academic information are available.
Main Flow
1.	System analyses student profile data.
2.	AI engine matches profile with available jobs.
3.	Recommended jobs are displayed on the dashboard.
4.	Student views suggested opportunities.
Postconditions
•	Personalized job recommendations are generated.
Acceptance Criteria
•	Recommendations should be relevant to student skills.
•	Recommendations update when profile data changes.

US-04: Job Posting by Recruiter
Actor
Recruiter
User Story
As a recruiter, I want to post job opportunities so that eligible students can apply.
Preconditions
•	Recruiter account must be approved.
•	Recruiter must be logged in.
Main Flow
1.	Recruiter selects "Create Job Posting".
2.	Recruiter enters job details.
3.	Recruiter specifies eligibility criteria.
4.	System validates information.
5.	Job posting becomes visible to students.
Postconditions
•	Job opportunity is published.
Acceptance Criteria
•	Job details are displayed correctly.
•	Eligibility criteria are visible to students.

US-05: Candidate Screening
Actor
Recruiter
User Story
As a recruiter, I want to filter applicants based on skills and eligibility criteria so that I can identify suitable candidates.
Preconditions
•	Students have applied for a job.
Main Flow
1.	Recruiter opens applicant list.
2.	Recruiter applies filters.
3.	System displays matching candidates.
4.	Recruiter reviews profiles and resumes.
Postconditions
•	Shortlisted candidates are identified.
Acceptance Criteria
•	Filtering results must be accurate.
•	Recruiter can view candidate details.

US-06: Placement Drive Management
Actor
Placement Officer
User Story
As a placement officer, I want to schedule and manage placement drives so that recruitment activities are conducted efficiently.
Preconditions
•	Recruiter information is available.
•	Placement officer is authenticated.
Main Flow
1.	Placement officer creates a placement drive.
2.	Drive details are entered.
3.	Eligible students are identified.
4.	Notifications are sent to students.
5.	Drive information is published.
Postconditions
•	Placement drive is successfully scheduled.
Acceptance Criteria
•	Students receive notifications.
•	Drive details are visible on the dashboard.



US-07: Placement Report Generation
Actor
Placement Officer
User Story
As a placement officer, I want to generate placement reports so that management can analyze placement performance.
Preconditions
•	Placement data must exist in the system.
Main Flow
1.	Placement officer selects report type.
2.	System gathers placement statistics.
3.	Report is generated.
4.	Report can be downloaded or viewed.
Postconditions
•	Placement report is available for analysis.
Acceptance Criteria
•	Reports contain accurate placement statistics.
•	Reports can be exported in PDF format.


